1
00:00:08,576 --> 00:00:12,580
She used to be homeless too.

2
00:00:16,717 --> 00:00:20,421
That statement
by the mysterious realtor, Kenji Rusudo,

3
00:00:20,488 --> 00:00:23,557
jolted the hearts of the people gathered

4
00:00:23,624 --> 00:00:25,526
at Bar Chichin Pui Pui.

5
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:28,729
For those who may be unaware,

6
00:00:28,796 --> 00:00:32,133
this is what happened some time ago.

7
00:00:32,199 --> 00:00:33,667
The other day,

8
00:00:33,734 --> 00:00:37,138
you said you were once homeless.
Is that true?

9
00:00:38,672 --> 00:00:42,276
Niwano couldn't help but remember
how beautiful Machi looked

10
00:00:42,343 --> 00:00:44,478
that day in the rain.

11
00:00:46,947 --> 00:00:49,150
This also happened some time ago.

12
00:00:49,717 --> 00:00:51,285
After my parents died,

13
00:00:52,186 --> 00:00:56,390
there was no adult who helped me.
Before I knew it, I had lost everything,

14
00:00:57,725 --> 00:00:59,393
and I was living in a park.

15
00:00:59,894 --> 00:01:03,764
And that was an incident
that even shook the heart

16
00:01:03,831 --> 00:01:06,467
of the endlessly thickheaded Mika.

17
00:01:07,902 --> 00:01:11,138
How does Mr. Rusudo know about that?

18
00:01:12,606 --> 00:01:13,841
It's so scary!

19
00:01:13,908 --> 00:01:15,576
SALES PERFORMANCE BOARD

20
00:01:19,246 --> 00:01:22,216
-Good morning.
-Good morning. You're early.

21
00:01:25,052 --> 00:01:27,922
If you're looking for Sangenya,
she's coming after meeting with a client.

22
00:01:33,060 --> 00:01:36,263
About what Rusudo said last night…

23
00:01:37,231 --> 00:01:38,065
What?

24
00:01:38,432 --> 00:01:39,366
Did you know about that?

25
00:01:40,468 --> 00:01:41,302
What?

26
00:01:41,368 --> 00:01:45,606
Well, you know, that Sangeya was…

27
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:49,243
living on the streets.

28
00:01:49,410 --> 00:01:50,711
I didn't know.

29
00:01:50,978 --> 00:01:52,646
-I'm sorry. I knew.
-Which is it?

30
00:01:52,713 --> 00:01:56,350
Sorry, I got confused since I wasn't sure
if it was okay for me to know.

31
00:01:56,417 --> 00:02:00,054
When did you hear about it?
Before Sangenya and I quit the company?

32
00:02:00,387 --> 00:02:01,222
Yes.

33
00:02:02,089 --> 00:02:04,358
I see. Is that right?

34
00:02:08,529 --> 00:02:10,931
I guess she really trusts you, huh?

35
00:02:11,932 --> 00:02:14,835
I only heard about that
after we got married.

36
00:02:16,237 --> 00:02:18,873
I don't know much about love and such,

37
00:02:19,039 --> 00:02:22,209
but maybe she couldn't
bring it up in front of you

38
00:02:22,276 --> 00:02:23,878
because she loves you so much.

39
00:02:24,478 --> 00:02:26,146
That's possible. Totally.

40
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:30,417
But why do you think
Rusudo knows about it?

41
00:02:30,484 --> 00:02:33,854
-Not sure.
-Give me something! Think about it!

42
00:02:33,921 --> 00:02:38,025
Okay. Maybe he's a corporate spy,

43
00:02:38,092 --> 00:02:40,160
or a public security police.

44
00:02:40,227 --> 00:02:43,931
Sangenya hasn't done anything
to be marked by the police.

45
00:02:43,998 --> 00:02:45,099
I'm sorry.

46
00:02:47,668 --> 00:02:51,639
Oh man, Chichin Pui Pui
is no longer a place where I can relax.

47
00:02:51,705 --> 00:02:52,907
Good morning.

48
00:02:53,607 --> 00:02:55,709
I sold the villa on the cliff.

49
00:02:55,776 --> 00:02:57,144
What? Already?

50
00:02:57,211 --> 00:03:00,080
Yes, because it's my job to sell houses.

51
00:03:00,147 --> 00:03:01,215
ON-SITE SALES WEEK

52
00:03:01,282 --> 00:03:03,417
During the On-Site Sales Week
that's starting today,

53
00:03:04,051 --> 00:03:06,687
we're featuring three properties
that have been difficult to sell.

54
00:03:06,754 --> 00:03:08,622
Let's all work hard together.

55
00:03:08,689 --> 00:03:09,523
Yes.

56
00:03:10,024 --> 00:03:13,494
The first property
is a house on a flag lot.

57
00:03:13,561 --> 00:03:16,230
This will be a tough one.

58
00:03:16,297 --> 00:03:19,233
Kagimura. Do you know what a flag lot is?

59
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,535
-Nope.
-I thought so.

60
00:03:22,503 --> 00:03:27,007
A flag lot only has a very small
entryway to the main road,

61
00:03:27,241 --> 00:03:29,677
and the plot is shaped like this.

62
00:03:29,743 --> 00:03:33,514
It looks like a flag on a pole,
and henceforth, the name "flag lot".

63
00:03:35,349 --> 00:03:39,720
Moreover, this pathway is narrow,
so the building can't be reconstructed.

64
00:03:39,787 --> 00:03:41,822
It's a non-rebuildable property.

65
00:03:41,889 --> 00:03:43,657
Yes, exactly that.

66
00:03:44,391 --> 00:03:47,027
And to make things worse,
it doesn't get much sunlight.

67
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:50,431
Man, this property
is a double, or triple whammy.

68
00:03:50,497 --> 00:03:54,301
This time, we must do
whatever it takes to sell this property!

69
00:03:55,035 --> 00:03:56,570
Mr. Fuse, you're in charge.

70
00:03:57,738 --> 00:03:58,572
And Adachi.

71
00:03:59,373 --> 00:04:01,976
I have a viewing appointment
for an apartment in Okubo.

72
00:04:02,042 --> 00:04:04,078
Work around your schedule.

73
00:04:04,411 --> 00:04:09,283
The second property used to be owned
by a former sumo wrestler.

74
00:04:09,550 --> 00:04:12,553
Everything in this house is very big.

75
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:15,089
Takuma and Kagimura are in charge of this.

76
00:04:15,155 --> 00:04:18,626
There's already one appointment
for a viewing, so make it count!

77
00:04:18,692 --> 00:04:20,527
-Yes, sir!
-Okay.

78
00:04:21,095 --> 00:04:24,431
The third property was once
the atelier of a former painter.

79
00:04:24,798 --> 00:04:28,769
On the ceiling are rails
that were used to hang lights.

80
00:04:28,969 --> 00:04:31,105
It's a bit of an eyesore
when used as a normal residence.

81
00:04:31,171 --> 00:04:34,575
Niwano and Hachinohe
are in charge of this one.

82
00:04:34,975 --> 00:04:35,809
-Yes.
-Yes.

83
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:41,348
Chief Sangeya, please support
the sales of these three properties.

84
00:04:41,415 --> 00:04:44,785
I will not give support.
When it comes down to it, I will sell it!

85
00:04:45,352 --> 00:04:47,154
Then please do that.

86
00:04:47,688 --> 00:04:50,991
Everyone, please get ready
and head to your locations.

87
00:04:51,058 --> 00:04:52,693
Do your best. Good luck.

88
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:55,162
-Yes.
-Yes, sir.

89
00:04:58,065 --> 00:05:00,267
Everyone, go at once! Go!

90
00:05:00,334 --> 00:05:01,702
Yes, ma'am!

91
00:05:05,272 --> 00:05:07,374
-Thanks for waiting.
-Thank you.

92
00:05:07,441 --> 00:05:09,009
This is pasta for you.

93
00:05:11,045 --> 00:05:14,014
If only this house next door
will sell their property,

94
00:05:14,081 --> 00:05:17,117
this flag lot can face the main road
and become prime real estate.

95
00:05:17,184 --> 00:05:19,553
That's exactly it, Adachi.

96
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:23,957
But the owner of this house
refuses to sell their property.

97
00:05:24,425 --> 00:05:27,161
-I see.
-Yup.

98
00:05:27,227 --> 00:05:29,897
But man, it's so cold.

99
00:05:29,963 --> 00:05:35,069
This weather is tough on a contract worker
who's close to retirement.

100
00:05:35,135 --> 00:05:37,204
You can rest in the living room inside.

101
00:05:37,705 --> 00:05:39,907
-Really?
-Go ahead.

102
00:05:39,973 --> 00:05:43,410
Then I think I'll do that.

103
00:05:43,477 --> 00:05:46,947
Adachi, you've been really nice lately.
You've got a new girlfriend?

104
00:05:51,719 --> 00:05:55,589
Whoa, it's so narrow.
Moving in will be a hassle.

105
00:06:00,661 --> 00:06:05,866
I wonder if I've become nicer
ever since I met Mr. Rusudo.

106
00:06:11,572 --> 00:06:14,908
Good morning. It's cold today.

107
00:06:14,975 --> 00:06:18,846
I was wondering how you're doing,
Mr. Rusudo.

108
00:06:22,015 --> 00:06:25,119
ON-SITE SALES EVENT NOW OPEN

109
00:06:33,327 --> 00:06:35,395
I'm doing on-site sales today!

110
00:06:42,636 --> 00:06:46,406
That's the flag lot
in Shimoigusa, isn't it?

111
00:06:46,673 --> 00:06:48,675
How did you know?

112
00:06:48,876 --> 00:06:50,477
ME-WOW!

113
00:06:50,978 --> 00:06:52,079
ME-WOW!

114
00:06:52,146 --> 00:06:53,847
I'm a realtor, remember?

115
00:06:54,181 --> 00:06:59,286
Even so, a normal realtor wouldn't be able
to tell the location with one picture.

116
00:07:01,855 --> 00:07:03,023
Ms. Sangenya!

117
00:07:03,857 --> 00:07:06,426
ON-SITE SALES EVENT

118
00:07:06,493 --> 00:07:08,762
I will sell this house!

119
00:07:26,814 --> 00:07:29,449
It's so unnecessarily big.

120
00:07:29,516 --> 00:07:32,820
-The sink is so high.
-What?

121
00:07:33,921 --> 00:07:35,122
That's so high!

122
00:07:35,189 --> 00:07:37,624
You won't be able to reach it, Mr. Takuma.

123
00:07:38,358 --> 00:07:39,560
Whatever!

124
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,995
Sumo wrestlers are really big, huh?

125
00:07:42,062 --> 00:07:45,232
Well, Hakuho is 192 cm,

126
00:07:45,299 --> 00:07:48,202
and Kisenosato is 188 cm.

127
00:07:48,268 --> 00:07:51,305
-You know a lot about sumo, huh?
-Not really.

128
00:07:51,371 --> 00:07:54,007
-Excuse me!
-That's our client!

129
00:07:55,342 --> 00:07:59,680
Hello, welcome. Please come inside.

130
00:08:01,815 --> 00:08:03,217
What's this?

131
00:08:03,517 --> 00:08:06,753
This is our company mascot, Sumo-kun!

132
00:08:07,354 --> 00:08:08,388
Dosukoi.

133
00:08:08,455 --> 00:08:09,556
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

134
00:08:10,624 --> 00:08:13,193
Oh wait, sir, please!

135
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:15,629
Please come inside and take a look.

136
00:08:15,696 --> 00:08:20,133
Welcome. We only have small slippers,
so please come in as you please.

137
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,869
We brought our own slippers.

138
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:28,909
Come inside. The living room here

139
00:08:28,976 --> 00:08:33,614
is three times the size
of a normal family sized property.

140
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:36,583
There are six gas valves too!

141
00:08:38,552 --> 00:08:42,289
This house can comfortably accommodate
numerous large people.

142
00:08:42,589 --> 00:08:47,127
The main bedroom on the second floor
is as big as this living room,

143
00:08:47,194 --> 00:08:49,863
and there are four guest rooms too!

144
00:08:50,163 --> 00:08:54,101
There are lots of drawers
specifically for storing kimonos.

145
00:08:54,167 --> 00:08:58,739
These cannot be found
in a normal residence.

146
00:08:59,306 --> 00:09:01,441
This is nice. Maybe I'll buy this place.

147
00:09:01,508 --> 00:09:03,310
Thank you.

148
00:09:04,278 --> 00:09:06,513
Who used to live here?

149
00:09:07,214 --> 00:09:11,718
The former ozeki,
Nishikigaminezeki, used to live here.

150
00:09:13,287 --> 00:09:14,688
That's bad news.

151
00:09:14,755 --> 00:09:18,825
Of all people, Nishikigaminezeki?
That's a bad omen.

152
00:09:19,359 --> 00:09:21,328
What do you mean?

153
00:09:21,528 --> 00:09:24,865
It means it's bad luck. You're aware of

154
00:09:24,932 --> 00:09:26,767
-Nishikigaminezeki's scandal, right?
-Yeah.

155
00:09:27,601 --> 00:09:30,470
-What did he do?
-Nishikigaminezeki

156
00:09:30,537 --> 00:09:33,307
is a dirty ozeki that got banished
from the sumo world

157
00:09:33,373 --> 00:09:37,010
after he got in a fight with someone
in Shibuya and caused serious injury.

158
00:09:37,077 --> 00:09:38,812
No way!

159
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:42,683
Enough! It's bad luck!
We won't buy this place.

160
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:44,985
Please wait a minute!

161
00:09:45,052 --> 00:09:47,220
Please stay! Stay for a minute!

162
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:50,590
One bedroom plus an atelier.

163
00:09:51,124 --> 00:09:54,861
It's not a bad property.
I wonder why it's not selling.

164
00:09:54,928 --> 00:09:57,931
FORMER PAINTER'S HOUSE

165
00:09:57,998 --> 00:10:01,435
I saw this property on the internet,
but can I take a look?

166
00:10:01,501 --> 00:10:04,404
Of course. Thank you for coming.

167
00:10:04,671 --> 00:10:06,239
Do you work out?

168
00:10:06,707 --> 00:10:08,041
Yes, a little.

169
00:10:08,308 --> 00:10:11,712
I'm Hachinohe from
Teiko Real Estate's Shinjuku Office.

170
00:10:11,778 --> 00:10:14,081
I'm Nakamaru from Adpension Advertisement.

171
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:15,782
I want a tour from you.

172
00:10:18,752 --> 00:10:22,756
This room here has a rather unique design.
Please come inside.

173
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:28,695
This is nice.

174
00:10:33,367 --> 00:10:36,970
If I place the machines here,
it'll be a great training room.

175
00:10:37,337 --> 00:10:40,240
Do you play some kind of sport?

176
00:10:40,307 --> 00:10:41,842
No, not really.

177
00:10:44,311 --> 00:10:46,713
I just want to maintain a beautiful body.

178
00:10:48,382 --> 00:10:49,549
Do you have a wife?

179
00:10:49,916 --> 00:10:51,852
-Nope.
-Do you plan to get married?

180
00:10:52,119 --> 00:10:54,688
Nope. Is it wrong that I'm not married?

181
00:10:54,755 --> 00:10:57,290
Not at all. Sorry for asking,
that was none of my business.

182
00:10:58,025 --> 00:10:59,326
Yeah, it sure isn't.

183
00:11:00,227 --> 00:11:01,528
I'm sorry.

184
00:11:02,129 --> 00:11:03,997
I'm gay.

185
00:11:04,865 --> 00:11:07,601
Oh… I see. That's nice.

186
00:11:08,068 --> 00:11:09,169
You really think it's nice?

187
00:11:10,103 --> 00:11:15,042
I think this is
a perfect property for you.

188
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:18,345
It's not that I want to stay single.

189
00:11:18,612 --> 00:11:21,314
Once I find someone I love,
I want to get married.

190
00:11:21,515 --> 00:11:24,184
But Article 24 of the Constitution says,

191
00:11:24,251 --> 00:11:28,855
"Marriage shall be based only
on the mutual consent of both sexes".

192
00:11:29,790 --> 00:11:30,624
You understand?

193
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:35,729
Same-sex marriage is not recognized
by Japan's Constitution.

194
00:11:36,763 --> 00:11:39,499
America, France, Germany,
and the Netherlands

195
00:11:39,566 --> 00:11:42,803
have legalized same-sex marriage,

196
00:11:43,437 --> 00:11:46,440
but gay couples
still can't get married in Japan.

197
00:11:47,674 --> 00:11:49,309
Is that right?

198
00:11:50,510 --> 00:11:53,447
As a realtor,
you should be aware of things like that.

199
00:11:54,214 --> 00:11:57,951
After all, one in every 13 people is LGBT.

200
00:11:58,718 --> 00:12:03,156
Then one in every 13 people
is someone like you?

201
00:12:03,557 --> 00:12:05,992
Do you have to look so shocked?
It's really rude.

202
00:12:06,326 --> 00:12:08,428
I'm sorry.

203
00:12:08,795 --> 00:12:13,066
Jeez. You're rude, ignorant,
and despicable.

204
00:12:14,301 --> 00:12:15,335
I'm very sorry.

205
00:12:15,402 --> 00:12:17,003
But I'll buy this house.

206
00:12:26,413 --> 00:12:27,414
Hey there.

207
00:12:30,117 --> 00:12:31,618
You came?

208
00:12:31,885 --> 00:12:33,253
I was nearby.

209
00:12:35,288 --> 00:12:37,724
This flag lot is hard to sell, isn't it?

210
00:12:37,791 --> 00:12:41,695
Yes, it is. And what's more,
Sanchi might steal this sale.

211
00:12:43,163 --> 00:12:45,198
Ms. Sangenya was here, huh?

212
00:12:50,370 --> 00:12:52,939
Things must be hard for you.
Do you want me to help you?

213
00:12:53,006 --> 00:12:55,475
No, I don't want to bother you.

214
00:12:56,042 --> 00:12:59,279
Tell me right away
if Ms. Sangenya does anything to you.

215
00:12:59,346 --> 00:13:01,982
Yes, I'll text you.

216
00:13:03,817 --> 00:13:07,187
Mr. Rusudo, you're quite stylish.

217
00:13:07,254 --> 00:13:09,556
You have two different socks on.

218
00:13:10,891 --> 00:13:15,128
What? I got them mixed up.

219
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:21,067
I guess we can't sell this house
to sumo wrestlers.

220
00:13:21,134 --> 00:13:24,604
Yeah, but I think it'll be equally hard
to sell it to a regular citizen too.

221
00:13:24,938 --> 00:13:26,606
Since it's unnecessarily big.

222
00:13:26,673 --> 00:13:28,141
How tiring.

223
00:13:29,242 --> 00:13:31,011
I'll see you next week at headquarters.

224
00:13:31,077 --> 00:13:32,779
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

225
00:13:34,481 --> 00:13:35,582
You sold the house already?

226
00:13:35,649 --> 00:13:39,119
No, but there's no point wearing Sumo-kun,
so I'm here to take it off.

227
00:13:39,186 --> 00:13:40,020
Ouch!

228
00:13:40,887 --> 00:13:41,922
-Manager.
-Huh?

229
00:13:41,988 --> 00:13:44,024
I sold the former painter's atelier.

230
00:13:44,591 --> 00:13:45,859
That was quick!

231
00:13:45,926 --> 00:13:48,361
Not Hachinohe, but I sold it.

232
00:13:49,229 --> 00:13:51,831
He's Sangenya's Children after all.

233
00:13:52,065 --> 00:13:54,568
Who bought the house?

234
00:13:54,634 --> 00:13:57,504
He's a gay macho who works
for an advertisement company.

235
00:13:58,772 --> 00:14:00,607
-LGBT?
-Yeah.

236
00:14:01,374 --> 00:14:02,609
TRAINING PROGRAM ABOUT LGBT

237
00:14:02,976 --> 00:14:06,479
There was a program about LGBT
at headquarters last week.

238
00:14:06,546 --> 00:14:08,448
What's LGBT?

239
00:14:09,149 --> 00:14:12,385
You really don't know anything, huh?

240
00:14:13,186 --> 00:14:16,056
"L" stands for lesbians.

241
00:14:16,122 --> 00:14:18,291
They're homosexual women.

242
00:14:19,426 --> 00:14:23,964
"G" stands for gays.
They're homosexual men.

243
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:26,199
"B" is for bisexuals.

244
00:14:26,533 --> 00:14:30,670
They're men and women
who are attracted to both sexes.

245
00:14:31,071 --> 00:14:35,709
And "T" stands for transgender.

246
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:40,780
In other words,
LGBT are sexual minorities.

247
00:14:40,847 --> 00:14:43,383
What's the trans thing?

248
00:14:43,917 --> 00:14:45,518
Transgender?

249
00:14:46,386 --> 00:14:49,956
You don't know that? Why are you
asking about the most difficult one?

250
00:14:50,023 --> 00:14:52,859
A transgender person is someone
who lives as or wants to live as

251
00:14:52,926 --> 00:14:55,929
a different gender than the one
he or she was registered as at birth.

252
00:14:56,196 --> 00:14:58,298
She appeared out of nowhere
like a phantom.

253
00:14:58,365 --> 00:15:00,533
You're so good with words.

254
00:15:00,934 --> 00:15:02,936
You explained it perfectly, Sangenya.

255
00:15:03,203 --> 00:15:05,405
Even if physical characteristics at birth

256
00:15:05,472 --> 00:15:08,808
register a child as a male,
and he is raised as a boy,

257
00:15:08,875 --> 00:15:11,711
he may always feel deep inside
that he is in fact a female.

258
00:15:11,778 --> 00:15:15,548
Such people are collectively known
as transgender people.

259
00:15:16,049 --> 00:15:16,916
Got it?

260
00:15:17,317 --> 00:15:22,389
Then the client I met today was gay,
so he's not transgender, right?

261
00:15:22,455 --> 00:15:23,590
That's right.

262
00:15:23,657 --> 00:15:26,760
No! A gay man is a male whose
sexual orientation, specifically,

263
00:15:26,826 --> 00:15:29,262
whom he is attracted to,
falls outside the majority,

264
00:15:29,329 --> 00:15:33,266
and a transgender person is someone whose
identity or how they perceive themselves

265
00:15:33,333 --> 00:15:36,236
falls outside the majority. Therefore,
there are gays among transgenders.

266
00:15:36,636 --> 00:15:38,872
I don't get it at all.

267
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:41,741
Some transgender people are unsure
whether they are male or female,

268
00:15:41,808 --> 00:15:44,944
are ambiguous about their gender,
or simply don't want to decide.

269
00:15:45,011 --> 00:15:46,546
This is all so difficult.

270
00:15:47,647 --> 00:15:52,652
Even so, every life that is born
into this world is equally precious.

271
00:15:52,719 --> 00:15:54,788
Just as the life
of genius realtor, Machi Sangenya,

272
00:15:54,854 --> 00:15:57,891
is as precious as the life
of lazy Kagimura, who is nothing

273
00:15:57,957 --> 00:16:00,293
but a burden
to the real estate brokerage division,

274
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:03,396
the lives of LGBT people
and the lives of those who are not

275
00:16:03,463 --> 00:16:06,299
are all equally precious.
Keep that in mind!

276
00:16:08,068 --> 00:16:09,035
Got it? Answer me!

277
00:16:09,736 --> 00:16:11,304
Yes, I will keep it in mind!

278
00:16:12,472 --> 00:16:15,909
Oh, I think Kagimura is the one
that needs to keep that in mind.

279
00:16:17,610 --> 00:16:21,281
Excuse me. I'm looking to buy a house.
Is this the right place?

280
00:16:21,348 --> 00:16:22,782
-Welcome.
-Welcome.

281
00:16:22,849 --> 00:16:23,983
-Niwano, help her.
-Yes.

282
00:16:24,617 --> 00:16:25,919
Toko, bring us tea.

283
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,887
QUESTIONNAIRE

284
00:16:29,089 --> 00:16:31,691
You're the technology director
at Goldman Prince?

285
00:16:31,758 --> 00:16:35,428
My husband works at the
Energy Business Unit of Marumoto & Co.,

286
00:16:35,495 --> 00:16:37,530
and I have a daughter
studying at a private junior high.

287
00:16:38,398 --> 00:16:40,900
Your family is pretty elite, huh?

288
00:16:41,835 --> 00:16:45,171
Up until now, we've both had a lot of
overseas business trips and assignments,

289
00:16:45,238 --> 00:16:47,607
so we thought living in
company housing was fine.

290
00:16:47,674 --> 00:16:50,910
But I'm starting to think
it might be time to buy our own house.

291
00:16:50,977 --> 00:16:55,482
I see. What kind of a house
do you have in mind?

292
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:59,252
I work for a foreign company,
so I want to host parties at my house.

293
00:16:59,753 --> 00:17:02,689
I don't care if it's a house
or an apartment, as long as

294
00:17:02,756 --> 00:17:05,592
there is a spacious area
where people can gather comfortably.

295
00:17:05,658 --> 00:17:09,129
Does your husband
have any special requests?

296
00:17:11,865 --> 00:17:14,934
My husband is very busy,
so he has left everything up to me.

297
00:17:16,903 --> 00:17:19,539
CHICHIN PUI PUI

298
00:17:25,979 --> 00:17:28,114
I'm so relieved that no one is here.

299
00:17:28,515 --> 00:17:30,917
But it's not good for my business.

300
00:17:30,984 --> 00:17:32,952
Should I turn around
and stay out of the way?

301
00:17:33,019 --> 00:17:37,557
Shirasu, you've matured enough to be able
to say something so considerate.

302
00:17:37,624 --> 00:17:39,926
I am a mother now, after all.

303
00:17:39,993 --> 00:17:44,464
When you were working at Teiko Real
Estate, you were an overwhelming presence

304
00:17:44,531 --> 00:17:46,599
in the sense
that you never learned to mature.

305
00:17:46,666 --> 00:17:48,501
That was so long ago.

306
00:17:48,735 --> 00:17:52,038
By the way, Kokoro,
does that guy Rusudo come here often?

307
00:17:52,105 --> 00:17:52,939
Yeah, once in a while.

308
00:17:54,774 --> 00:17:57,677
There's something a bit scary about him.

309
00:17:57,744 --> 00:18:01,147
It's as if he's trying to bring
Sanchi down by spreading false rumors.

310
00:18:01,214 --> 00:18:05,985
Shirasu, it's the first time in history
that our opinions have aligned.

311
00:18:06,519 --> 00:18:09,656
I know she's your wife,
but I find Sanchi hard to deal with.

312
00:18:09,722 --> 00:18:13,726
But between her and Mr. Rusudo,
I think he is scarier.

313
00:18:14,060 --> 00:18:15,562
I think there's a dark side to him.

314
00:18:16,463 --> 00:18:17,430
A dark side, huh?

315
00:18:17,497 --> 00:18:20,366
He doesn't seem that complex to me.

316
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:22,135
-I disagree.
-I disagree.

317
00:18:22,202 --> 00:18:23,837
He's shrouded in darkness.

318
00:18:23,903 --> 00:18:26,906
-Yeah, definitely.
-For sure.

319
00:18:27,674 --> 00:18:31,144
As requested, the layout features
a bright, south-facing design

320
00:18:31,211 --> 00:18:32,912
with spacious openings.

321
00:18:32,979 --> 00:18:36,115
You're right. It looks wonderful.

322
00:18:39,052 --> 00:18:40,787
I think she'll seal the deal.

323
00:18:41,254 --> 00:18:44,090
I'm sorry, I'm late.

324
00:18:44,457 --> 00:18:48,294
I think this is a really nice place.
This is the owner.

325
00:18:48,495 --> 00:18:51,397
She is Tomoyo Kurumada. She's my cousin,
and we'll be living together.

326
00:18:52,999 --> 00:18:54,734
Tomo, come this way.

327
00:18:56,503 --> 00:19:00,106
This is the bedroom.

328
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:01,808
Isn't it nice?

329
00:19:04,544 --> 00:19:08,515
And over here…

330
00:19:11,684 --> 00:19:13,720
The bathroom.

331
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:16,356
Isn't it nice and bright?

332
00:19:16,890 --> 00:19:20,693
Stop doing that here.

333
00:19:21,895 --> 00:19:25,365
No, not right now. Oh jeez.

334
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:35,542
What are you guys doing?
You lied? You guys aren't cousins?

335
00:19:35,975 --> 00:19:38,978
I will not sell this house to you two!

336
00:19:39,646 --> 00:19:40,613
Mr. Kawabe.

337
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:45,285
This apartment is filled with memories
of living here with my wife,

338
00:19:45,351 --> 00:19:46,452
who recently passed away.

339
00:19:48,354 --> 00:19:53,960
My wife won't be able to rest in peace
if I sell this place to some lesbians.

340
00:19:54,027 --> 00:19:55,595
I'm afraid that's discrimination…

341
00:19:55,662 --> 00:19:57,163
Then are you okay with it?

342
00:19:58,932 --> 00:20:00,767
Who decided

343
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:04,504
that men should love women,
and women should love men?

344
00:20:04,671 --> 00:20:06,539
-Stop it.
-Why?

345
00:20:06,606 --> 00:20:10,977
A man should love a woman,
and a woman should love a man.

346
00:20:11,044 --> 00:20:12,612
God decided that.

347
00:20:12,679 --> 00:20:16,683
True love can exist between
couples of the same sex.

348
00:20:17,083 --> 00:20:19,419
We're a same sex couple,

349
00:20:19,485 --> 00:20:23,790
but we contribute to society and we
haven't done anything to be ashamed of.

350
00:20:24,090 --> 00:20:28,595
But I will not sell this house to you.

351
00:20:29,062 --> 00:20:30,496
I hope you understand.

352
00:20:31,464 --> 00:20:33,800
-Mr. Kawabe.
-Forget him!

353
00:20:34,467 --> 00:20:36,102
I don't want this house.

354
00:20:38,304 --> 00:20:39,772
Thank you for waiting.

355
00:20:41,708 --> 00:20:46,713
The owners of these four properties
won't be rude like that last one, right?

356
00:20:46,779 --> 00:20:48,381
Most likely not.

357
00:20:49,082 --> 00:20:52,285
Mr. Adachi, you don't think it's
a serious concern that some people

358
00:20:52,352 --> 00:20:54,153
won't sell houses to lesbians?

359
00:20:54,387 --> 00:20:57,290
Not at all. Everyone has a right
to buy a house.

360
00:20:57,557 --> 00:20:59,993
Stop it, Tomo.

361
00:21:00,059 --> 00:21:03,997
If you hadn't done something uncalled for,
we could've bought that apartment.

362
00:21:04,063 --> 00:21:09,335
Uncalled for?
Why can't you be proud of who you are?

363
00:21:09,936 --> 00:21:14,641
Are we supposed to be ashamed
of the fact that we love each other?

364
00:21:15,174 --> 00:21:17,810
I don't want to continue
arguing about this issue.

365
00:21:17,877 --> 00:21:22,382
I just want to love my partner peacefully
without causing friction with others.

366
00:21:22,448 --> 00:21:27,086
We don't have to fight the world
in order to get people to accept us.

367
00:21:27,153 --> 00:21:30,957
I don't agree with that.
I can't stand the fact we have to face

368
00:21:31,024 --> 00:21:33,559
prejudice, discrimination,
and pushback for trying to buy a house.

369
00:21:33,726 --> 00:21:35,695
Then do what you want.

370
00:21:35,962 --> 00:21:39,632
I will find the perfect place

371
00:21:39,699 --> 00:21:41,934
for Ms. Mashima and Ms. Kurumada.

372
00:21:42,335 --> 00:21:43,503
Who are you?

373
00:21:43,870 --> 00:21:45,538
I am a realtor.

374
00:21:46,439 --> 00:21:47,940
Don't steal my client!

375
00:21:48,341 --> 00:21:49,409
What's going on?

376
00:21:49,475 --> 00:21:51,878
-You won't be able to handle those two.
-Why?

377
00:21:51,944 --> 00:21:53,546
I can find new properties for them.

378
00:21:53,613 --> 00:21:56,149
-What's going on?
-Niwano, we're going.

379
00:21:57,684 --> 00:21:58,518
What's going on?

380
00:22:01,854 --> 00:22:03,389
What's going on?

381
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:08,327
What's going on?

382
00:22:09,395 --> 00:22:11,030
Stop snooping!

383
00:22:11,831 --> 00:22:13,466
Why?

384
00:22:14,967 --> 00:22:19,739
I'm sorry for the sudden interruption
by Sangenya.

385
00:22:20,473 --> 00:22:23,743
I will find the perfect property
that will please both of you,

386
00:22:23,810 --> 00:22:27,146
so I ask that you continue
to rely on me as your realtor.

387
00:22:28,815 --> 00:22:32,852
That's fine.
I just hate doing things in secrecy.

388
00:22:35,254 --> 00:22:37,356
I understand how you feel.

389
00:22:38,424 --> 00:22:39,892
Are you two gay?

390
00:22:42,795 --> 00:22:46,399
This is Mr. Rusudo, a freelance realtor.

391
00:22:46,666 --> 00:22:51,370
I came to help find a home
for Adachi's precious client.

392
00:22:52,171 --> 00:22:53,406
I'm right, aren't I?

393
00:22:55,041 --> 00:22:56,242
I wonder.

394
00:22:57,143 --> 00:23:00,146
Why are you hiding it?
You two look so good together.

395
00:23:00,213 --> 00:23:03,316
Be loud and proud.

396
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:04,584
I'm back.

397
00:23:05,585 --> 00:23:07,820
It took a while at the bank.

398
00:23:07,887 --> 00:23:10,923
They said they'll find a place
a lot better than the last one.

399
00:23:12,525 --> 00:23:13,760
Who is that?

400
00:23:13,826 --> 00:23:14,961
He's Mr. Adachi's partner.

401
00:23:15,862 --> 00:23:17,663
Oh my, I see.

402
00:23:19,265 --> 00:23:20,133
By the way,

403
00:23:21,801 --> 00:23:22,935
what do you think of this?

404
00:23:29,175 --> 00:23:30,309
It's nice.

405
00:23:31,344 --> 00:23:33,780
-I'll buy it for you as a gift.
-What?

406
00:23:41,854 --> 00:23:42,722
MARUMOTO & CO.

407
00:23:42,789 --> 00:23:45,658
This is the company where
Mrs. Manami Kimura's husband works.

408
00:23:45,725 --> 00:23:48,594
Go to the reception desk
and have Mrs. Kimura's husband come down.

409
00:23:48,961 --> 00:23:51,330
I know he works at
the Energy Business Unit,

410
00:23:51,397 --> 00:23:53,566
but I didn't get his name.

411
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:57,170
Just ask for Mr. Kimura
from the Energy Business Unit.

412
00:23:57,370 --> 00:23:59,839
-You're right.
-You're getting rusty.

413
00:24:00,506 --> 00:24:01,474
Sorry.

414
00:24:05,344 --> 00:24:08,181
Hold on. Mrs. Kimura
said that her husband is very busy,

415
00:24:08,247 --> 00:24:11,284
so he left all the house hunting
matters up to her.

416
00:24:11,350 --> 00:24:12,785
Is it okay to talk to him?

417
00:24:13,052 --> 00:24:14,387
This is to sell a house.

418
00:24:15,521 --> 00:24:19,025
Tell the receptionist that you're Tanaka,
who has an appointment with him at 16:30.

419
00:24:19,592 --> 00:24:20,426
Tanaka?

420
00:24:20,493 --> 00:24:23,129
-Get to it! Go!
-Yes, ma'am!

421
00:24:24,030 --> 00:24:28,301
I have an appointment with Mr. Kimura
from the Energy Business Unit.

422
00:24:28,367 --> 00:24:30,336
My name is Tanaka.

423
00:24:30,403 --> 00:24:32,471
Please wait one moment.

424
00:24:34,607 --> 00:24:37,577
He will be here shortly.
Please wait over there.

425
00:24:39,779 --> 00:24:43,916
They said he's coming down.
I wonder why he agreed to come down.

426
00:24:43,983 --> 00:24:46,886
Everyone has an acquaintance named Tanaka.

427
00:24:48,154 --> 00:24:50,022
-Let's hide.
-What?

428
00:24:55,027 --> 00:24:58,097
Why are we hiding
when he's coming down to meet us?

429
00:24:58,164 --> 00:24:59,532
Use your brain.

430
00:25:05,872 --> 00:25:06,973
-Hey there.
-Hello.

431
00:25:07,039 --> 00:25:08,040
Where's Mr. Tanaka?

432
00:25:08,107 --> 00:25:09,442
He's waiting over there.

433
00:25:09,508 --> 00:25:10,610
Thank you.

434
00:25:11,143 --> 00:25:12,612
It's him.

435
00:25:13,846 --> 00:25:15,848
Just remember his face.

436
00:25:16,215 --> 00:25:17,316
I apologize.

437
00:25:21,053 --> 00:25:22,588
-He's not here.
-What?

438
00:25:23,289 --> 00:25:25,625
MARUMOTO & CO.

439
00:25:27,159 --> 00:25:30,296
-Don't miss him.
-Yes, ma'am.

440
00:25:43,342 --> 00:25:45,678
He went the opposite direction
from the station.

441
00:26:00,059 --> 00:26:02,328
He went into room 301.

442
00:26:09,535 --> 00:26:11,837
It's a woman's place, huh?

443
00:26:15,107 --> 00:26:18,344
I think we should sell a house
to Mrs. Manami Kimura

444
00:26:18,411 --> 00:26:21,347
without delving into their business.

445
00:26:21,414 --> 00:26:23,783
That's why you can't sell houses, Niwano.

446
00:26:24,083 --> 00:26:27,286
I sold a house yesterday.

447
00:26:27,853 --> 00:26:30,523
Don't get cocky just because
you sold one house.

448
00:26:31,257 --> 00:26:32,091
Yes, ma'am.

449
00:26:37,530 --> 00:26:38,731
Who is it?

450
00:26:39,332 --> 00:26:40,733
I'm a realtor.

451
00:26:46,973 --> 00:26:49,408
You're Mr. Takeshi Kimura, I presume?

452
00:26:53,879 --> 00:26:56,015
Please call me Kyoko when you're here.

453
00:26:56,649 --> 00:26:59,752
Ms. Kyoko, may we come in?

454
00:27:07,460 --> 00:27:11,230
This is steamed red bean jelly
I made yesterday.

455
00:27:11,564 --> 00:27:13,199
-Steamed red bean jelly?
-Yes.

456
00:27:13,265 --> 00:27:14,133
Thank you.

457
00:27:19,338 --> 00:27:23,642
I didn't know that my wife
was thinking of buying a house.

458
00:27:24,844 --> 00:27:29,648
Most likely, your wife is planning
to buy a house and take out a loan

459
00:27:29,715 --> 00:27:34,653
so that she can keep you close to them

460
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:36,922
as a husband and a father.

461
00:27:38,791 --> 00:27:41,360
I adore my daughter,

462
00:27:41,927 --> 00:27:46,232
and I believe it's my responsibility
to raise her until she's an adult.

463
00:27:46,832 --> 00:27:50,102
Of course, my wife is important to me too.

464
00:27:50,936 --> 00:27:57,143
But on the other hand, I am a woman.
Every day, I find it harder

465
00:27:57,643 --> 00:28:00,613
to suppress my desire
to live my life as a woman.

466
00:28:06,585 --> 00:28:08,487
May I ask one question?

467
00:28:09,221 --> 00:28:10,322
What is it?

468
00:28:10,389 --> 00:28:14,326
When you go back home to your family,
do you go there as a man?

469
00:28:14,393 --> 00:28:16,762
Do you go back home as Mr. Takeshi Kimura?

470
00:28:17,229 --> 00:28:20,366
Yes. Since my wife begged me

471
00:28:20,433 --> 00:28:23,269
to act as a father
in front of our daughter.

472
00:28:24,036 --> 00:28:28,374
I'm worried about whether my daughter
will be able to accept this side of me.

473
00:28:28,674 --> 00:28:32,344
That's why I always end up
acting the role of a masculine father.

474
00:28:33,345 --> 00:28:36,949
The company where I work is very
old-fashioned, so even if I came out,

475
00:28:37,016 --> 00:28:39,318
I don't think anyone will understand me.

476
00:28:39,919 --> 00:28:44,423
I really hate having to wear men's suits.

477
00:28:45,524 --> 00:28:48,961
But I still endure it
and work hard all day.

478
00:28:49,195 --> 00:28:54,166
The few hours I spend here before going
home is the only time I can be myself.

479
00:28:55,968 --> 00:29:00,639
I can't call a place a home
if I have to go back there as a man.

480
00:29:01,407 --> 00:29:05,244
I don't mind buying a house
if I can live there as a woman.

481
00:29:10,049 --> 00:29:13,452
Mr. Kimura is transgender, huh?

482
00:29:13,652 --> 00:29:14,520
Yes.

483
00:29:15,855 --> 00:29:17,490
He was so sincere.

484
00:29:20,126 --> 00:29:22,795
Isn't it better for them to get a divorce?

485
00:29:23,762 --> 00:29:26,165
-Niwano.
-Yes?

486
00:29:26,398 --> 00:29:27,833
What's your job?

487
00:29:28,567 --> 00:29:30,169
To sell properties.

488
00:29:30,236 --> 00:29:32,605
Then just focus on selling properties.

489
00:29:32,671 --> 00:29:35,040
It's not your job
to solve people's problems.

490
00:29:39,645 --> 00:29:41,580
This is so cute!

491
00:29:41,647 --> 00:29:44,350
This is so popular.
It'll look so good on you!

492
00:29:44,416 --> 00:29:46,585
I used this month's allowance already.

493
00:29:48,587 --> 00:29:50,222
-It's too bad.
-Yeah.

494
00:29:58,097 --> 00:30:01,200
I'm back. I'll be going out again
once I drop off my things.

495
00:30:01,834 --> 00:30:03,369
Something this large

496
00:30:03,869 --> 00:30:05,404
doesn't belong to either me or Mitsuki.

497
00:30:09,008 --> 00:30:11,810
-Oh my, sorry, that's mine.
-Stop talking like a woman.

498
00:30:12,111 --> 00:30:15,347
I strictly told you not to bring
your life as a woman into this house.

499
00:30:16,215 --> 00:30:18,984
You're probably leaving these things
to make me accept you,

500
00:30:20,286 --> 00:30:25,024
but how do you think Mitsuki will feel
when she finds out that these are yours?

501
00:30:26,759 --> 00:30:29,094
I really don't know what to do anymore.

502
00:30:30,429 --> 00:30:32,531
I don't think I can keep
hiding this forever.

503
00:30:32,598 --> 00:30:33,766
You have to!

504
00:30:34,900 --> 00:30:39,205
-Mitsuki is young and at a difficult age.
-I know that!

505
00:30:40,005 --> 00:30:45,644
But it's painful for me
to continue living as a father.

506
00:30:47,413 --> 00:30:50,449
I won't allow you to live
as anything other than her father.

507
00:30:51,617 --> 00:30:55,287
I don't care how hard and painful it is.
In this house, you have to be a father.

508
00:30:57,656 --> 00:31:02,027
I heard that you're
planning to buy a house.

509
00:31:03,062 --> 00:31:04,296
The realtor came to visit me.

510
00:31:05,397 --> 00:31:08,467
-Yeah, I'm buying a house.
-It's fine if you want to buy a house.

511
00:31:09,868 --> 00:31:15,674
But if you're going to expect me
to be a man inside the house…

512
00:31:18,043 --> 00:31:19,445
I can't do it.

513
00:31:21,814 --> 00:31:23,382
Don't cry!

514
00:31:24,583 --> 00:31:25,618
I'm home.

515
00:31:25,684 --> 00:31:27,353
-Welcome back.
-Welcome home.

516
00:31:28,187 --> 00:31:31,023
I have work related things to attend to,
so I'll be going now.

517
00:31:31,290 --> 00:31:32,958
-Bye.
-Bye.

518
00:31:33,626 --> 00:31:35,160
Dad is busy, huh?

519
00:31:42,301 --> 00:31:43,869
I'm back.

520
00:31:43,936 --> 00:31:45,471
-Welcome back.
-Welcome back.

521
00:31:45,537 --> 00:31:47,940
What's with that hat, Adachi?

522
00:31:48,641 --> 00:31:52,177
Isn't it strange? He's been
wearing it all day since this morning.

523
00:31:52,244 --> 00:31:53,545
Doesn't it look nice?

524
00:31:53,612 --> 00:31:55,180
I mean, it looks stylish, but…

525
00:31:55,247 --> 00:32:00,519
That's not the right hat
to wear with a suit.

526
00:32:01,353 --> 00:32:02,488
It's hilarious.

527
00:32:02,888 --> 00:32:05,224
How are things going
with the on-site sales, Mr. Fuse?

528
00:32:05,691 --> 00:32:11,263
Things are very difficult. After all,
it's a non-rebuildable flag lot.

529
00:32:12,731 --> 00:32:15,401
Takuma and Kagimura,
how's the former sumo wrestler's house?

530
00:32:15,467 --> 00:32:16,869
-Well…
-Impossible.

531
00:32:17,202 --> 00:32:19,371
Don't give up so easily!

532
00:32:19,438 --> 00:32:22,274
Everyone should work together
no matter which house you're in charge of,

533
00:32:22,474 --> 00:32:24,143
so that we can sell these houses.

534
00:32:24,743 --> 00:32:25,678
Yes!

535
00:32:27,780 --> 00:32:28,914
-Yes!
-Yes!

536
00:32:31,583 --> 00:32:37,256
And Niwano, how's it going
with Mrs. Manami Kimura's house?

537
00:32:38,390 --> 00:32:42,094
Manager, I'm realizing
that LGBT people have it very tough.

538
00:32:42,161 --> 00:32:44,396
She's LGBT?

539
00:32:44,463 --> 00:32:47,433
No, her husband is a transgender.

540
00:32:47,499 --> 00:32:49,768
What? But they're still married?

541
00:32:49,968 --> 00:32:53,739
They're technically still married,
but as a wife, she's having a hard time

542
00:32:53,806 --> 00:32:56,141
understanding her husband
who wants to be a woman.

543
00:32:56,475 --> 00:32:58,110
I don't understand it either.

544
00:32:58,544 --> 00:33:01,046
It's only natural that you can't
understand other people's feelings.

545
00:33:03,115 --> 00:33:06,285
It's arrogant to even think
that you can understand other people.

546
00:33:06,618 --> 00:33:10,622
You're right.
Mika Shirasu and I had two kids together,

547
00:33:10,689 --> 00:33:13,292
but we couldn't
understand each other at all.

548
00:33:14,493 --> 00:33:18,797
And I find it hard to believe that Manager
and Sangenya understand each other.

549
00:33:18,864 --> 00:33:23,469
Well, what I understand is
that I am not able to fully

550
00:33:23,535 --> 00:33:26,638
understand my own wife.

551
00:33:26,705 --> 00:33:28,640
I see.

552
00:33:29,041 --> 00:33:31,377
Well, I'll be going now.

553
00:33:31,443 --> 00:33:32,878
-Thank you.
-Bye.

554
00:33:32,945 --> 00:33:35,180
I worked so hard today.

555
00:33:35,247 --> 00:33:37,216
Niwano, we should get going too.

556
00:33:37,282 --> 00:33:39,318
Niwano still has work left to do.

557
00:33:39,385 --> 00:33:42,254
Is that right? Then Takuma and Hachinohe,
what about you guys?

558
00:33:42,321 --> 00:33:44,423
I made plans to watch a movie
with my wife.

559
00:33:44,490 --> 00:33:46,825
Mika Shirasu told me to make dinner
for the kids.

560
00:33:48,260 --> 00:33:49,395
What about you, Adachi?

561
00:33:49,928 --> 00:33:51,029
I…

562
00:33:51,096 --> 00:33:53,732
Oh, you have fencing?

563
00:33:53,799 --> 00:33:55,467
Sorry, I'll be going now.

564
00:33:55,534 --> 00:33:57,603
I'll be going too.

565
00:33:59,505 --> 00:34:03,942
Then I guess I'll leave by myself.

566
00:34:07,379 --> 00:34:08,547
Bye.

567
00:34:08,614 --> 00:34:10,916
Ms. Sangenya, you're okay with that?

568
00:34:10,983 --> 00:34:12,618
What do you mean by that?

569
00:34:12,684 --> 00:34:13,919
Because poor Manager Yashiro--

570
00:34:13,986 --> 00:34:15,621
Mind your own business!

571
00:34:15,687 --> 00:34:16,922
Bye.

572
00:34:17,389 --> 00:34:18,457
Wait!

573
00:34:19,958 --> 00:34:24,596
Mr. Takuma, Mr. Hachinohe,
Niwano, Kagimura. Report your sizes.

574
00:34:24,663 --> 00:34:25,764
Sizes?

575
00:34:26,098 --> 00:34:29,134
The size of your bust, waist, and hip.

576
00:34:29,401 --> 00:34:30,602
For what?

577
00:34:30,936 --> 00:34:33,138
To sell a house.

578
00:34:34,940 --> 00:34:37,743
If you don't know your size,
I will measure you right now!

579
00:34:41,180 --> 00:34:44,216
Today was another good workout,
wasn't it, Mr. Rusudo?

580
00:34:45,484 --> 00:34:46,785
Call me Kenji.

581
00:34:50,422 --> 00:34:53,625
Then please call me Satoshi.

582
00:34:57,629 --> 00:34:58,864
Satoshi.

583
00:35:03,569 --> 00:35:05,137
The moon is beautiful.

584
00:35:08,574 --> 00:35:09,475
You're right.

585
00:35:11,310 --> 00:35:14,079
Um… Kenji…

586
00:35:16,615 --> 00:35:18,817
Are you seeing anyone right now?

587
00:35:19,051 --> 00:35:19,885
No.

588
00:35:22,387 --> 00:35:23,388
Why?

589
00:35:23,689 --> 00:35:26,758
I was just curious, that's all.

590
00:35:27,192 --> 00:35:30,095
Did you think
there was more to that question?

591
00:35:33,699 --> 00:35:37,870
After all, one can never understand
other people's feelings.

592
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:44,910
Sanchi said the same thing at work today.

593
00:35:47,112 --> 00:35:51,517
"It's only natural that you can't
understand other people's feelings.

594
00:35:52,751 --> 00:35:56,288
It's arrogant to even think
that you can understand other people."

595
00:35:58,457 --> 00:36:02,127
Well said, Machi Sangenya.

596
00:36:04,162 --> 00:36:06,365
But I feel that
trying to understand someone

597
00:36:06,431 --> 00:36:11,069
even while knowing that
true mutual understanding is impossible,

598
00:36:12,237 --> 00:36:13,605
is basically

599
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:18,043
what it means to like someone.

600
00:36:21,580 --> 00:36:23,015
You're right.

601
00:36:33,825 --> 00:36:34,927
This was on you.

602
00:36:38,397 --> 00:36:40,332
So I…

603
00:36:41,333 --> 00:36:43,869
I kind of forgot what I wanted to say.

604
00:36:45,170 --> 00:36:48,073
Either way,
I think Sanchi is a cold person.

605
00:36:49,207 --> 00:36:52,477
-Is that so?
-I think so.

606
00:36:56,248 --> 00:36:57,616
You may be right.

607
00:37:20,906 --> 00:37:23,041
I found the perfect house for you,
Mrs. Kimura.

608
00:37:23,809 --> 00:37:26,979
I would like to take you there right now.
Can you come?

609
00:37:27,446 --> 00:37:28,480
Right now?

610
00:37:28,714 --> 00:37:30,949
Yes, right now.

611
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:44,796
Thank you for coming.

612
00:37:47,666 --> 00:37:48,900
What happened, Mr. Niwano?

613
00:37:49,267 --> 00:37:50,969
Please step inside.

614
00:37:56,408 --> 00:37:58,276
This is the living room.

615
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:05,550
There are six gas valves
in this living room.

616
00:38:05,617 --> 00:38:08,086
It's right here.

617
00:38:08,153 --> 00:38:10,822
Mrs. Manami, since you work
at Goldman Prince,

618
00:38:11,056 --> 00:38:13,291
this room will be perfect for you

619
00:38:13,358 --> 00:38:17,529
to welcome foreigners as guests
with a grand Japanese hot pot party.

620
00:38:19,598 --> 00:38:21,133
Let's go to the kitchen.

621
00:38:22,968 --> 00:38:27,606
The high countertop, sink, and stove

622
00:38:27,673 --> 00:38:31,810
is perfect for when
Mr. Takeshi wants to cook.

623
00:38:31,877 --> 00:38:33,512
He will not be cooking at home.

624
00:38:34,413 --> 00:38:35,781
Let's move on.

625
00:38:40,886 --> 00:38:44,990
This room has drawers
designed specifically for kimonos.

626
00:38:46,625 --> 00:38:51,229
It's the perfect place to store
all of Mr. Takeshi's kimonos.

627
00:38:51,430 --> 00:38:56,368
Hey, what I asked for is a house
to live in with my male husband.

628
00:38:57,035 --> 00:38:59,337
We don't need drawers
to put away his kimonos.

629
00:38:59,404 --> 00:39:02,607
How do you like this house, Mr. Takeshi?

630
00:39:03,008 --> 00:39:05,477
It's making me uncomfortable. I'm leaving.

631
00:39:06,144 --> 00:39:08,313
Mr. Niwano, what is going on here?

632
00:39:10,615 --> 00:39:13,385
How dare you guys dress up like that
to mock my husband?

633
00:39:13,452 --> 00:39:14,653
I've had enough!

634
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:16,822
Everyone, leave.

635
00:39:18,590 --> 00:39:22,728
Do you think you showed understanding
by dressing up like that?

636
00:39:25,130 --> 00:39:27,966
You guys don't understand it at all.

637
00:39:29,334 --> 00:39:33,538
He loves both me and my daughter,

638
00:39:34,439 --> 00:39:38,577
but it pains him
when he is treated by society

639
00:39:38,643 --> 00:39:41,246
as a father, a husband, and a man.

640
00:39:44,583 --> 00:39:48,887
You guys will never understand
the pain he has to endure.

641
00:39:48,954 --> 00:39:50,689
You'll never understand our pain.

642
00:39:50,889 --> 00:39:51,723
I don't!

643
00:39:53,492 --> 00:39:55,594
Unfortunately, I don't understand.

644
00:39:56,628 --> 00:40:01,266
I don't understand
either of your feelings.

645
00:40:01,566 --> 00:40:07,005
But the both of you understand each other.

646
00:40:08,540 --> 00:40:12,477
You understand each other's
pain and hardships.

647
00:40:13,044 --> 00:40:16,114
Although you two may not continue on
as husband and wife,

648
00:40:16,648 --> 00:40:19,785
I think it's best if you live here
while supporting

649
00:40:19,851 --> 00:40:22,921
and helping each other
as one individual to another.

650
00:40:23,155 --> 00:40:24,523
What do you think?

651
00:40:27,893 --> 00:40:32,430
If it was just me, I could accept him
and help him as one individual to another.

652
00:40:33,665 --> 00:40:37,602
After all,
he's sincere and very kind-hearted.

653
00:40:38,837 --> 00:40:42,707
I already knew, without you telling me,
that it's best to support each other.

654
00:40:43,341 --> 00:40:45,544
But our daughter
is still in middle school,

655
00:40:46,344 --> 00:40:49,114
so I don't want her to get confused
when her father

656
00:40:49,347 --> 00:40:51,950
suddenly announces
that he's going to be a woman.

657
00:40:52,617 --> 00:40:57,422
Her high school entrance exam
is coming up, and she's an adolescent.

658
00:40:57,689 --> 00:40:59,357
I know I'll have no choice

659
00:40:59,858 --> 00:41:01,860
but to leave if Mitsuki turns me away.

660
00:41:02,894 --> 00:41:06,198
I don't want to cause any hindrance
as Mitsuki grows into adulthood.

661
00:41:07,899 --> 00:41:12,237
But just once, I want to have
an honest heart-to-heart talk with her.

662
00:41:14,639 --> 00:41:15,807
Miss Mitsuki,

663
00:41:16,875 --> 00:41:20,478
you heard what Mr. Takeshi said.
What do you say?

664
00:41:28,854 --> 00:41:30,422
I don't care at all.

665
00:41:30,722 --> 00:41:33,191
I already knew
that you were transgender, Dad.

666
00:41:34,226 --> 00:41:38,063
You always notice the slightest changes
in my clothes and hairstyles.

667
00:41:38,129 --> 00:41:42,400
When I told my friends,
all of them said they were so jealous.

668
00:41:42,667 --> 00:41:45,737
Plus, I have a classmate at school
who's just like you.

669
00:41:45,937 --> 00:41:49,608
Whether there's a mom and dad at home
or it's two moms at home,

670
00:41:49,975 --> 00:41:51,576
it doesn't make any difference to me.

671
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:59,150
Lately, on job application forms,
you're given a choice

672
00:41:59,217 --> 00:42:04,189
to choose from "male,"
"female," or "I'd rather not say."

673
00:42:05,056 --> 00:42:07,225
Many schools provide students with options

674
00:42:07,292 --> 00:42:09,961
of whether to wear skirts or pants
as their school uniform.

675
00:42:10,829 --> 00:42:16,601
Miss Mitsuki lives a normal life
in an era that embraces diversity.

676
00:42:21,940 --> 00:42:26,845
There are many different ways in which
people can cooperate and live together.

677
00:42:27,846 --> 00:42:30,348
At this moment, the Kimura family

678
00:42:30,849 --> 00:42:34,252
now consists of two mothers
and Miss Mitsuki.

679
00:42:34,319 --> 00:42:36,721
Your family has been reborn
as a brand new team.

680
00:42:37,923 --> 00:42:40,992
Mrs. Manami Kimura, Ms. Kyoko…

681
00:42:41,059 --> 00:42:43,428
Your name is Kyoko? Wow.

682
00:42:43,962 --> 00:42:48,333
Will you buy this house
for 86 million yen?

683
00:42:52,437 --> 00:42:53,571
-Yes.
-Yes.

684
00:42:54,606 --> 00:42:55,874
I've got them.

685
00:42:57,375 --> 00:43:04,049
-Mr. Takuma.
-Please sign your name here. This way.

686
00:43:04,382 --> 00:43:05,317
Yes.

687
00:43:05,383 --> 00:43:06,851
What do you want me to call you?

688
00:43:06,918 --> 00:43:09,421
Call me Kyoko.

689
00:43:11,289 --> 00:43:14,326
It feels like I'm the only one
getting the short end of the stick.

690
00:43:15,593 --> 00:43:19,431
A sumo wrestler used to live here
with his attendants.

691
00:43:19,497 --> 00:43:21,466
So there's a total of five bedrooms.

692
00:43:21,700 --> 00:43:24,803
In the future, even when both of you
find new partners,

693
00:43:24,869 --> 00:43:26,972
there will be enough rooms for everyone.

694
00:43:27,572 --> 00:43:29,674
A new partner?

695
00:43:30,375 --> 00:43:31,843
You sure say some crazy things.

696
00:43:32,644 --> 00:43:34,813
I don't think it's that crazy.

697
00:43:38,283 --> 00:43:41,152
Ms. Sangenya, thanks for this hoodie.

698
00:43:41,219 --> 00:43:44,556
This is so popular.
It'll look so good on you!

699
00:43:44,622 --> 00:43:46,591
I used this month's allowance already.

700
00:43:46,658 --> 00:43:47,993
Too bad.

701
00:43:48,526 --> 00:43:49,995
It suits you.

702
00:43:50,929 --> 00:43:54,065
Thank you for your business.

703
00:43:54,866 --> 00:43:56,534
I'll be going now.

704
00:43:58,536 --> 00:44:00,338
It went just as you predicted.

705
00:44:00,405 --> 00:44:04,209
Of course. I'm off to sell another house.

706
00:44:04,776 --> 00:44:07,846
Niwano, report to Manager
that this house has been sold.

707
00:44:08,279 --> 00:44:09,814
Yes, ma'am.

708
00:44:09,881 --> 00:44:11,683
ON-SITE SALES EVENT

709
00:44:14,953 --> 00:44:17,555
That narrow path from the main road
to this house

710
00:44:17,622 --> 00:44:20,692
is the path that leads to your hidden,
secret romantic hideout.

711
00:44:22,494 --> 00:44:25,764
The front entrance is only
partially visible from the main road,

712
00:44:26,064 --> 00:44:29,434
so you can be lovey-dovey by the door
when you see each other off.

713
00:44:29,901 --> 00:44:33,705
I don't want to do things in secrecy.

714
00:44:33,772 --> 00:44:37,876
This is a property that will
simultaneously meet the needs for both

715
00:44:37,942 --> 00:44:42,147
the modest Ms. Mashima
and the passionate Ms. Kurumada.

716
00:44:42,213 --> 00:44:45,583
You're just trying
to make it sound convincing.

717
00:44:46,551 --> 00:44:49,154
How can you ever understand how we feel?

718
00:44:49,220 --> 00:44:51,623
Ms. Mashima, Ms. Kurumada.

719
00:44:52,624 --> 00:44:56,828
It's only natural that you can't
understand other people's feelings.

720
00:45:00,965 --> 00:45:05,670
It's arrogant to even think
that you can understand other people.

721
00:45:05,904 --> 00:45:07,772
I've heard that before somewhere.

722
00:45:07,839 --> 00:45:12,477
That's why I've been saying
that I want to live in peace and quiet,

723
00:45:12,777 --> 00:45:15,880
without having to argue
with people who don't understand us.

724
00:45:15,947 --> 00:45:17,882
That kind of compromise

725
00:45:17,949 --> 00:45:20,919
is what contributes
to the difficulties of our lives.

726
00:45:22,087 --> 00:45:25,490
Both of you refuse
to change your opinions.

727
00:45:26,257 --> 00:45:31,129
You guys are trying to force
your own opinion on each other.

728
00:45:31,963 --> 00:45:36,935
You two are incapable of compromising
or understanding each other.

729
00:45:38,103 --> 00:45:41,272
But Ms. Mashima, and Ms. Kurumada,

730
00:45:41,339 --> 00:45:45,343
you two still intensely desire
and love each other.

731
00:45:47,679 --> 00:45:51,416
Love is contradictory like that.

732
00:45:58,256 --> 00:46:01,860
Even if one party compromises
and agrees with the other,

733
00:46:02,193 --> 00:46:05,997
that doesn't mean they've truly
understood each other,

734
00:46:06,064 --> 00:46:08,433
so problems will eventually surface.

735
00:46:09,834 --> 00:46:13,705
Therefore, by living
in this secluded house,

736
00:46:13,771 --> 00:46:18,676
Ms. Mashima can fully enjoy
displaying love in a quiet and modest way.

737
00:46:18,910 --> 00:46:24,349
While outside, Ms. Kurumada
can proudly embrace Ms. Mashima,

738
00:46:24,649 --> 00:46:27,051
and stick to her own ideals.

739
00:46:28,019 --> 00:46:33,258
This way, you two will live your life
asserting your own beliefs.

740
00:46:34,025 --> 00:46:37,896
If you arrogantly think that you can
fully understand each other,

741
00:46:39,030 --> 00:46:41,199
that idea needs to be thrown away
right here right now!

742
00:46:42,066 --> 00:46:43,201
Sanchi.

743
00:46:45,403 --> 00:46:50,808
We can quietly love each other here
despite our differences in opinion…

744
00:46:51,075 --> 00:46:53,945
While outside I will openly
show my affection for you.

745
00:46:55,346 --> 00:46:57,382
But she doesn't really like it.

746
00:46:57,448 --> 00:47:01,886
Even if you two argue
and quarrel, it's all right,

747
00:47:02,854 --> 00:47:04,722
because you two love each other.

748
00:47:06,124 --> 00:47:07,959
Well, I guess so.

749
00:47:09,060 --> 00:47:13,765
Ms. Mashima, do you like this house?

750
00:47:15,833 --> 00:47:16,868
I like it.

751
00:47:17,902 --> 00:47:20,338
If you like it, then I'm on board too.

752
00:47:22,540 --> 00:47:24,275
-Adachi.
-Yes.

753
00:47:26,444 --> 00:47:28,813
Ms. Mashima, Ms. Kurumada.

754
00:47:28,880 --> 00:47:32,684
Will you buy this house
for 18 million yen?

755
00:47:34,018 --> 00:47:35,086
-Yes.
-Yes.

756
00:47:36,187 --> 00:47:37,555
Thank you.

757
00:47:38,122 --> 00:47:40,992
-All right, Adachi, get the contract.
-Yes.

758
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:44,862
Kenji Rusudo.

759
00:47:55,406 --> 00:47:58,643
Oh man, I'm exhausted.

760
00:47:58,710 --> 00:48:00,845
But putting on make-up was kind of fun.

761
00:48:01,179 --> 00:48:03,281
Hey, who used all this?

762
00:48:03,348 --> 00:48:04,215
It was Niwano.

763
00:48:04,282 --> 00:48:05,283
-Niwano.
-Unbelievable!

764
00:48:05,350 --> 00:48:07,252
Please buy your own.

765
00:48:08,553 --> 00:48:11,456
I sold the flag lot.

766
00:48:12,757 --> 00:48:16,828
Good job! That was the most
problematic property this time.

767
00:48:16,894 --> 00:48:19,764
You did well, Adachi. You too, Mr. Fuse.

768
00:48:20,198 --> 00:48:24,802
Ms. Sangenya, I sold the flag lot.

769
00:48:24,869 --> 00:48:26,004
Is that right?

770
00:48:26,070 --> 00:48:29,674
I mean technically speaking,
that Rusudo guy sold it.

771
00:48:29,741 --> 00:48:31,409
What do you mean by that?

772
00:48:31,476 --> 00:48:34,979
Mr. Fuse! I sold it, didn't I?

773
00:48:35,046 --> 00:48:37,248
-Um… So…
-Hold on.

774
00:48:37,315 --> 00:48:39,083
Explain what you meant by that.

775
00:48:41,786 --> 00:48:43,321
I guess it doesn't matter.

776
00:48:43,655 --> 00:48:48,226
After all, we sold three problematic
properties during the on-site sale.

777
00:48:48,459 --> 00:48:52,230
Since the on-site sales
were a big success,

778
00:48:52,297 --> 00:48:54,299
let's go out for drinks!

779
00:48:54,365 --> 00:48:56,567
I'm tired, so I'm leaving.

780
00:48:56,634 --> 00:48:58,436
-Me too.
-What?

781
00:48:58,503 --> 00:49:00,371
-Bye.
-See you tomorrow.

782
00:49:00,438 --> 00:49:02,006
-What?
-Bye.

783
00:49:02,073 --> 00:49:04,342
-Manager.
-Yeah?

784
00:49:04,409 --> 00:49:08,212
Manager, you and I
will be going home together.

785
00:49:10,348 --> 00:49:11,616
Right.

786
00:49:16,120 --> 00:49:18,423
Thanks to your help,

787
00:49:18,489 --> 00:49:20,658
I didn't lose against Sanchi.

788
00:49:20,725 --> 00:49:21,959
I'm happy for you.

789
00:49:24,896 --> 00:49:25,930
Um…

790
00:49:27,098 --> 00:49:31,269
Why are you so nice to me?

791
00:49:34,238 --> 00:49:37,008
Because I want to capture
Ms. Sangenya's attention.

792
00:49:37,942 --> 00:49:38,776
What?

793
00:49:39,143 --> 00:49:42,714
I'm a Machi Sangenya specialist.

794
00:49:43,448 --> 00:49:45,450
Machi Sangenya specialist?

795
00:49:46,784 --> 00:49:48,453
That's why I know

796
00:49:48,853 --> 00:49:53,057
what methods Ms. Sangenya
would use to sell houses.

797
00:50:08,439 --> 00:50:12,243
Um… You know…

798
00:50:12,310 --> 00:50:18,282
Um… Who is…

799
00:50:18,349 --> 00:50:19,517
Kenji Rusudo?

800
00:50:20,284 --> 00:50:21,452
I don't know.

801
00:50:22,086 --> 00:50:23,121
You don't know?

802
00:50:24,789 --> 00:50:25,857
I don't know.

803
00:50:36,300 --> 00:50:37,135
I will not pay!

804
00:50:37,201 --> 00:50:39,203
If you don't buy our house,
I'm cutting ties with you.

805
00:50:39,270 --> 00:50:42,173
Go ahead and cut off ties
that are only connected through money!

806
00:50:42,240 --> 00:50:45,343
Will you buy this house
for 70 million yen?

807
00:50:45,410 --> 00:50:46,244
Mr. Rusudo?

808
00:50:46,310 --> 00:50:47,145
It's time to fight.

809
00:50:47,211 --> 00:50:48,479
You betrayed me?

810
00:50:48,546 --> 00:50:49,480
Will you counterattack?

811
00:50:49,547 --> 00:50:50,848
I lost.
